pg"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":1,"forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":0,"can_add":1,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"steps":[{"id":739031,"guid":"09CF7D50710C11E99DFD935622A10696","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"26FCD6AE0C484604BEE453A3062A60B8","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Acquisition of Data"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F01655571F4A4542AB79B86F69C5A665","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare and culture experimental samples, negative process control, and positive process control according to your desired experimental procedure.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0},{"id":739032,"guid":"09D6D050710C11E99DFD935622A10696","previous_id":739031,"previous_guid":"09CF7D50710C11E99DFD935622A10696","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"DCAD70DEAD214A348832C47F466D1A35","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Acquisition of Data"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"865A5ACF55AC4E22B164F27BE44F6BD5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare experimental samples, negative process control, and positive process control as needed for running through your flow cytometer.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0},{"id":739033,"guid":"09D6F760710C11E99DFD935622A10696","previous_id":739032,"previous_guid":"09D6D050710C11E99DFD935622A10696","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"DFF3D102E5EF41338964BAC229648F1E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Acquisition of Data"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6D34350780874155A7DA5A2FE722BD82","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Shake SpheroTech rainbow calibration beads vigorously or vortex briefly. Prepare bead sample by diluting 15 \u03bcL of SpheroTech rainbow calibration beads into 200 \u03bcL of 1x PBS.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0},{"id":739034,"guid":"227BDD80710C11E99DFD935622A10696","previous_id":739033,"previous_guid":"09D6F760710C11E99DFD935622A10696","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6DA310288CA44BDA9D4E91A20F26DDC2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Acquisition of Data"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"EFF6D71390824D3A91BEC9F2BAE3DC40","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Measure all samples in flow cytometer<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Using the bead sample, adjust MEFL channel voltage so that the top bead peak is below detector saturation.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Using the negative process control sample, adjust forward-scatter and side-scatter voltages to place the strong cell peak as close to the center of the detector range as possible (see example illustrated below).<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Instrument gating should be set to ensure that no cell events are discarded (see example illustrated below).<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Collect at least 10,000 events per sample.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Using the negative process control sample, adjust forward-scatter and side-scatter voltages to place the strong cell peak as close to the center of the detector range as possible (see example illustrated below).<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Instrument gating should be set to ensure that no cell events are discarded (see example illustrated below).<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Collect at least 10,000 events per sample.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bgr65af6.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:center\"><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Instrument gating should be set to ensure that no cell events are discarded (see example illustrated below).<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Collect at least 10,000 events per sample.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bgr75af6.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"43F14C0CF2724F528B79FB9B5002C853","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bgr65af6.png\" \/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"8A4A9BDC73DE45D78464663A1431105D","order_id":3,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bgr75af6.png\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0},{"id":739035,"guid":"BE5CF4A0710C11E99DFD935622A10696","previous_id":739034,"previous_guid":"227BDD80710C11E99DFD935622A10696","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EA22187F533848D2B6CFE8D40E81AB4E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Acquisition of Data"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"61FB37B9456C406880184613FB7E25EE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Compute the MEFL\/a.u. scaling factor from bead sample either using one of the tools on the <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">Measurement resources page<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> or following the Excel-based scaling factor computation below.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0},{"id":739036,"guid":"CE3A8A40710C11E99DFD935622A10696","previous_id":739035,"previous_guid":"BE5CF4A0710C11E99DFD935622A10696","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D5AD530941BE4EF48C56FB7F5F9F958E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Acquisition of Data"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E1C43D232D7A4630B7CB940648B258D1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Multiply all fluorescence measurements by MEFL\/a.u. scaling factor to convert from a.u. to MEFL.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0},{"id":739037,"guid":"48126770710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","previous_id":739036,"previous_guid":"CE3A8A40710C11E99DFD935622A10696","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7952CD056C5E48E48F8FD15374B6762E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Excel-based scaling factor computation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FD7B4491A95C4060BFEB6AF9A1033983","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Compute a histogram of GFP channel measurements for the rainbow calibration bead sample; this should show some number of distinct high peaks (as in the example below).<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bgse5af6.png\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"5296BB45407D431FB14B77AEDE27C293","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bgse5af6.png\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0},{"id":739039,"guid":"90414160710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","previous_id":739037,"previous_guid":"48126770710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7EA1EC4BBE814FEBB9BFADDEEE707AA3","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Excel-based scaling factor computation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1D58EE84AC494C0EBB3048988689A97E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Identify the center of each distinct, narrow, high peak, and record these locations in the provided cell of the Fluorescence Calibration spreadsheet, starting with the highest peak. Leave all other locations blank. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"18EEB210716611E9945AAFE2673B3BAF","order_id":2,"type_id":23,"title":"file","source":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bgs24df6.xlsx","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/extensions\/xlsx.png","original_name":"iGEM Data Analysis Template - Flow Cytometry Fluorescence Calibration - v1.xlsx"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0},{"id":739040,"guid":"905565A0710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","previous_id":739039,"previous_guid":"90414160710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5EDBAB7404254EA8AF0228135C23EA9B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Excel-based scaling factor computation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B59B33DF1FEF4A50A540296CA748F821","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Select the model and channel for your calibration beads from the menu in the sheet.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0},{"id":739041,"guid":"905565A1710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","previous_id":739040,"previous_guid":"905565A0710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8F060E3466784A118608AE6B8E7338AD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Excel-based scaling factor computation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"550BBCA71DE642CC816689A0D0587BC9","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Record the lot number for your calibration beads (e.g., \u201cAJ02\u201d) in the provided cell. This should cause a set of bead values to appear. The lot number must precisely match the lot in the \u201cBead Catalog\u201d sheet.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0},{"id":739042,"guid":"90558CB0710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","previous_id":739041,"previous_guid":"905565A1710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"731D604E10C84FE3B4FF3EAD4D83D264","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Excel-based scaling factor computation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B7B958D4B52945799A3352ED6414BA01","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The MEFL\/a.u. scaling factor and the graph on the sheet should now fill in.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0},{"id":739043,"guid":"90558CB1710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","previous_id":739042,"previous_guid":"90558CB0710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D47D252BA26B40BD847453871A6FE97B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Excel-based scaling factor computation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4ADE4235AC5C40578842F8413D4C3C24","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The graph shows one point for each peak and a line for the MEFL\/a.u. scaling factor.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0},{"id":739044,"guid":"90558CB2710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","previous_id":739043,"previous_guid":"90558CB1710D11E9A823BD7FF0111A78","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"74524805752B4DC0A86CE29499253F61","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Excel-based scaling factor computation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"EF1B4A2639CA4A65B3F8F904EE3A44B7","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Check that the points are all close to the line (as in the example below). If this is not the case, check to be sure that you have identified and recorded your peaks correctly.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"duration":0}],"materials":[{"id":203098,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Rainbow calibration beads","linfor":null,"url":"http:\/\/www.spherotech.com\/CalibrationParticles.htm","sku":"RCP-30-5A","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"SpheroTech","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/www.spherotech.com","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":664},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":203099,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Rainbow calibration beads","linfor":null,"url":"http:\/\/www.spherotech.com\/CalibrationParticles.htm","sku":"URCP-38-2K","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"SpheroTech","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/www.spherotech.com","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":664},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":203100,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Rainbow calibration beads","linfor":null,"url":"http:\/\/www.spherotech.com\/CalibrationParticles.htm","sku":"URQP-38-6K","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"SpheroTech","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/www.spherotech.com","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":664},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol can be applied to any strain of cell that can be safely run through a flow cytometer. For clarity, we have written it assuming E. coli DH5-alpha; to apply the protocol to another cell type, substitute the other cell type for any place where the protocol says [E. coli DH5-alpha].<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol has been written for measurement of GFP, YFP, or other yellow\/green fluorescent proteins into MEFL units. To apply it to fluorescent proteins of other colors:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Replace BBa_J364001 with a construct for strong expression of the other protein. <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>For blue proteins (e.g., <\/span><a style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":UNDERLINE;\">mTagBFP<\/span><\/a><span>), measure with 405nm excitation and 450nm\/50nm emission filter. Units will be MEC30.<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>For red\/orange proteins (e.g., <\/span><a style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":UNDERLINE;\">mCherry<\/span><\/a><span>), measure with 561nm excitation and 610nm\/20nm or 620nm\/15nm emission filter. \u00a0Units will be MEPTR.<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">For far-red \/ near-infrared proteins (e.g., IRFP), measure with 635nm excitation and 780nm\/60nm or 750nm long-pass (LP) emission filter. Units will be MEAPCY7.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>To apply the protocol to multiple colors, add a positive process control for each color and use one of the tools on the <\/span><a style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;:UNDERLINE;\">iGEM Measurement Resources page<\/span><\/a><span> to compensate measurements for spectral overlap.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol can be combined with bead-based cell size calibration.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1557302400}